    <note>Qian(1) Xie [145] Posthumously purged as Yuanyou coalition member. Yi's [146] grandson, Yanyuan's [7010] son. Entered the civil service via brother-in-law, Zhang(1) Shengqing's [275] memorial. Father-in-law was Lu(1) Jujian [1300] (a son of Lu(1) Mengzheng [8101]). Xie was Wang(2) Xiaodi's [8148] father-in-law, Zeng(1) Ji's [1692] grandfather-in-law. In 1069, Xie was #2 on a decree exam. XCB, 307.17a, 309.3a, 321.3a, 466.8b, 468.5b, 469.6b, 474.7a, 477.7a, 484.12a, 493.3b; Xianchun Linan zhi, 65.9a; Li Gang, WJ, 167.4b-16b (funerary inscription delayed because of his inclusion in the Yuanyou dang stele). CBD, 5, 4067-8.</note>
